
How to run it
=============
1) Setup:
- Get web.py 0.23. It is used to render the templates:
$ wget http://webpy.org/static/web.py-0.23.tar.gz
$ tar xzf web.py-0.23.tar.gz
$ ln -s webpy/web web

- Get a Google App Engine account:
http://appengine.google.com/

- Change application name inside app.yaml
application: your-app-name


2) Test it locally:
$ path/to/google_appengine/dev_appserver.py .

$ firefox http://localhost:8080


3) Deploy it on App Engine:
$ path/to/google_appengine/appcfg.py update .

$ firefox http://your-app-name.appspot.com


4) Ensure refreshing of the feeds:
$ wget http://your-app-name.com/compute
    ... do it regularly (use cron or http://host-tracker.com/ )

